This model is similar to that of the low temperature magnetic structure of Fe$_5$SiB$_2$ \cite{Cedervall-Fe5SiB2}, which has a layered structure with magnetic moments aligned along the Fe-B-layer in the structure. A recent M\"ossbauer study on a textured sample ($b$-axis out of the plane) of AlFe$_2$B$_2$ suggests that the magnetic moments are in the $ab$-plane, with an angle of \textless 40\textdegree\ from the $b$-axis \cite{AlFe2B2-Mossbauer}. That there is no magnetic order along the $c$-direction is in support of the model presented in this paper, but the neutron diffraction data does not show any magnetic contributions indicating a $b$-component.


